item.title: Victoria braces for more wild winds
item.description: Just days after a deadly storm wreaked havoc and killed three people across Melbourne, wild winds are again expected to hit Victoria.

item.title: Man skips quarantine to go to the pub
item.description: A Perth pub has been shut down due to a COVID-19 breach with police telling patrons they must self-isolate.

item.title: Brave shoppers intervene in axe attack
item.description: Two men have been seriously injured after they were allegedly attacked at a shopping centre on Melbourne’s Mornington Peninsula.

item.title: How we know vaccines are safe
item.description: With COVID-19 impacting the global population, and causing millions of deaths, researchers around the world are racing to find a vaccine.

item.title: Stabbed teen dies in hospital
item.description: Homicide detectives are investigating after a teenage boy died as a result of being stabbed near Geelong last Sunday night.

item.title: Thousands still without power after storm
item.description: At least 13,000 homes and businesses are still without power after a deadly storm swept across Melbourne.

item.title: Qld’s swipe at ScoMo over baby death
item.description: Queensland Deputy Premier Steven Miles took a swipe at Scott Morrison on Saturday, after questions about the tragic death of an unborn baby.

item.title: Covidiot found ‘hiding in bushes’
item.description: A man caught hiding in the bushes from police after going to a mate’s place to watch the footy was among the Melburnians fined for breaking virus restrictions on Friday.

item.title: ‘Today not the day’: Open up plan on hold
item.description: Victoria still has a long way to go before a plan can be finalised to ease restrictions, Premier Daniel Andrews says.

item.title: Sydney CBD virus cluster grows
item.description: New South Wales has recorded 14 cases of COVID-19 in the past 24 hours, bringing the state’s total number of infections to 3844.
